imdb.plot outline: Hello Stranger is a contemporary snapshot of the people of Australia. We talk to people in the street... then follow one story home. People pass each other everyday, but rarely stop to say hello. It turns out that we are more complex, remarkable and much stranger than you've ever imagined. Filming in all corners of the country, from Arnhem Land to the banks of the Murray river in SA, and from the housing commissions of Redfern to Caville Avenue in Surfers Paradise, Hello Stranger interviewed over 300 Australians cast directly off the streets.
